Package: DEP2
Title: Differential Enrichment analysis of Proteomics data
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Arne", "Smits", email = "smits.arne@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person("Wolfgang", "Huber", email = "wolfgang.huber@embl.de", role = "aut"),
    person("Feng", "Zhenhuan", email = "feng_zhenhuan@gibh.ac.cn",role = "aut"))
Description: DEP2 is the improved package of DEP, a previous one probiding an
    intergrated analysis workflow for mass spectrometry proteomics data for differential
    protein expression or differential enrichment.It requires tabular input (e.g. txt files) 
    as generated by quantitative analysis softwares of raw mass spectrometry data, 
    such as MaxQuant or IsobarQuant. We add funtions for PTM analysis, TMT result 
    analysis, biological function analysis. Besides, we recomposed the visual functions 
    to make it easier to customize. In order to provide a easy-going but more powerful 
    tools for biologists, we combine few sessions in shiny app, and writing detailed documentations.
